text: Saint-Aubin-sur-Quillebeuf is a commune in the Eure department in Normandy in northern France. The village was formerly called Wambourg (Wamburgum 1025, Weneborch 1147) and Saint-Aubin-de-Vambourg. The name was Anglo-Saxon in origin. ==Population== ==See also== *Communes of the Eure department ==References== *INSEE Category:Communes of Eure
